unrelated `entomologist-data` branches break `sync`

* Create a git repo "Origin" that does not have an `entomologist-data`
  branch.

* Clone "Origin" into local repo "A" and local repo "B".

* In local repo A, create a local `entomologist-data` branch with an
  issue in it, e.g. by running `ent new "first issue"`.

* Sync ent in local repo A to origin.

* In local repo B, create a local `entomologist-data` branch with e.g.
  `ent list` or `ent new "blah"`.

* In local repo B, try to sync with origin. This *fails* because the two
  `entomologist-data` branches have unrelated histories.
